[Docs](https://element-plus.org/en-US/component/time-select.html#attributes)

jlg-time-select/clear-icon.description:
custom clear icon component, default: CircleClose.

[Docs](https://element-plus.org/en-US/component/time-select.html#attributes)

jlg-time-select/min-time.description:
minimum time, any time before this time will be disabled

[Docs](https://element-plus.org/en-US/component/time-select.html#attributes)

jlg-time-select/max-time.description:
maximum time, any time after this time will be disabled

[Docs](https://element-plus.org/en-US/component/time-select.html#attributes)

jlg-time-select/format.description:
set format of time, default: HH:mm.

[Docs](https://element-plus.org/en-US/component/time-select.html#attributes)

jlg-time-select/change.description:
triggers when user confirms the value

[Docs](https://element-plus.org/en-US/component/time-select.html#events)

jlg-tooltip/append-to.description:
which element the tooltip CONTENT appends to

[Docs](https://element-plus.org/en-US/component/tooltip.html#attributes)

jlg-tooltip/effect.description:
Tooltip theme, built-in theme: `dark` / `light`, default: dark.

[Docs](https://element-plus.org/en-US/component/tooltip.html#attributes)

jlg-tooltip/content.description:
display content, can be overridden by `slot#content`, default: ''.

[Docs](https://element-plus.org/en-US/component/tooltip.html#attributes)

jlg-tooltip/raw-content.description:
whether `content` is treated as HTML string, default: false.

[Docs](https://element-plus.org/en-US/component/tooltip.html#attributes)

jlg-tooltip/fallback-placements.description:
list of possible positions for Tooltip [popper.js](https://popper.js.org/docs/v2/modifiers/flip/#fallbackplacements)

[Docs](https://element-plus.org/en-US/component/tooltip.html#attributes)

jlg-tooltip/show-after.description:
delay of appearance, in millisecond, default: 0.

[Docs](https://element-plus.org/en-US/component/tooltip.html#attributes)

jlg-tooltip/show-arrow.description:
whether the tooltip content has an arrow, default: true.

[Docs](https://element-plus.org/en-US/component/tooltip.html#attributes)

jlg-tooltip/hide-after.description:
delay of disappear, in millisecond, default: 200.

[Docs](https://element-plus.org/en-US/component/tooltip.html#attributes)

jlg-tooltip/auto-close.description:
timeout in milliseconds to hide tooltip, default: 0.

[Docs](https://element-plus.org/en-US/component/tooltip.html#attributes)

jlg-tooltip/popper-class.description:
custom class name for Tooltip's popper

[Docs](https://element-plus.org/en-US/component/tooltip.html#attributes)

jlg-tooltip/enterable.description:
whether the mouse can enter the tooltip, default: true.

[Docs](https://element-plus.org/en-US/component/tooltip.html#attributes)

jlg-tooltip/teleported.description:
whether tooltip content is teleported, if `true` it will be teleported to where `append-to` sets, default: true.

[Docs](https://element-plus.org/en-US/component/tooltip.html#attributes)

jlg-tooltip/trigger.description:
How should the tooltip be triggered (to show), default: hover.

[Docs](https://element-plus.org/en-US/component/tooltip.html#attributes)

jlg-tooltip/virtual-triggering.description:
Indicates whether virtual triggering is enabled

[Docs](https://element-plus.org/en-US/component/tooltip.html#attributes)

jlg-tooltip/virtual-ref.description:
Indicates the reference element to which the tooltip is attached

[Docs](https://element-plus.org/en-US/component/tooltip.html#attributes)

jlg-tooltip/trigger-keys.description:
When you click the mouse to focus on the trigger element, you can define a set of keyboard codes to control the display of tooltip through the keyboard, default: ['Enter','Space'].

[Docs](https://element-plus.org/en-US/component/tooltip.html#attributes)

jlg-tooltip/persistent.description:
when tooltip inactive and `persistent` is `false` , popconfirm will be destroyed

[Docs](https://element-plus.org/en-US/component/tooltip.html#attributes)
